05/03/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Leaders of the Croatian Democratic Union, the senior ruling coalition partner, proposed on Wednesday (March 4th) cutting public sector wages by 10% in response to the global financial and economic crisis. 
The cuts would affect all positions, including members of parliament, cabinet ministers and every other government post. 
The government has already announced it intends to save money where possible, including in state-owned companies. 
It has also unveiled an ambitious stimulus package. 
(AFP, HINA, HRT - 04/03/09)
